xstream

Class Slot

  • java.lang.Object
    • xstream.Slot
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<Slot>

    public class Slot
extends Object
implements Comparable<Slot>
    A time slot contains a series of events whose timestamps form a monotonic sequence and metadata about the timeslot such as time range of the events and slot index.
    Maximum number of events in a slot is fixed, though events can vary in structure and storage.
    A slot is a row in a timeseries database table.
    Author:
    pinaki poddar
